data.title: Junior AI Systems Engineer
data.descriptionHtml:
Looking for a Full Stack developer able to build an AI-powered care ecosystem that integrates therapy, coaching, education, and support... where every AI agent knows how to hold space.

About Anywhere Clinic

At Anywhere Clinic, we have a team of Psychiatrists, Physician Assistants, Psychologists, Therapists, and other specialists to help patients achieve their mental health goals. Our goal is to approach care in a holistic manner, only resorting to medications when necessary. We offer competitive compensation and allow for much collaboration between our clinical team members. We look forward to meeting you!

Description

Description:
Anywhere Clinic – Holistic Healing at Scale, Powered by AI Systems
We’re building the future of mental health:
Not just an app.
A healing system.
An AI-powered care ecosystem that integrates therapy, coaching, education, and support, where every AI agent knows how to hold space.
We're not just replacing roles.
We’re evolving them.
So that every human on our team, and every patient we serve, gets more time for what matters most: healing, presence, and growth.

Who You Are:
You’re a Junior AI engineer or systems architect who:
  • Knows GPT, LangChain, and vector memory, but also gets what a client in crisis might need
  • Believes in automation with empathy
  • Builds tools that actually serve human healing, not just productivity
  • Has shipped real-world projects, ideally in health, wellness, or creative tech
  • Thinks in workflows, not just models, how AI can think, respond, triage, and uplift
You're not here to optimize clicks.
You're here to evolve care.

What You’ll Build:
  • AI Therapist Assistants: AI guided self-therapy support, intake, journaling, and reflection
  • Coaching Agents: Trained to respond to patient scenarios with therapeutic language and safety protocols
  • AI-Led Education Tools: Agents that teach core mental health frameworks and mirror human coaching dynamics
  • System Automation: Replace admin overhead with thoughtful AI - scheduling, triage, insurance verification, billing
  • AI Receptionists that answer with empathy
  • Scheduling Optimizers that balance patient schedules to minimize schedule gaps and lower no show rates
  • Therapeutic AI Scribes that write notes with assessment and treatment plan output guides for provider and client
  • Marketing Outreach Agents that connect former patients and future leads to care

Tech Stack (Flexible, Evolving):
  • OpenAI GPT-4 API, LangChain, Pinecone/Weaviate for vector search
  • Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG), memory systems, fine-tuning
  • Backend: Python/FastAPI or similar
  • Optional: emotion detection, voice transcription, avatar animation

The Offer:
  • $60k to 90k base salary
  • Work with visionary doctors, therapists, and thought leaders
  • Remote-first, mission-aligned, high-integrity team
  • A deep mission, not just a job

Who Is the Right Fit:
You’ve always wanted to work on something that feels like both code and healing.
You want to look back and say I helped rewire healthcare for good.
You're the kind of engineer who:
  • Knows LLM pipelines but also meditates
  • Believes AI isn’t dangerous if it’s built with values
  • Wants their work to make people feel and grow

Apply Now:
We’re not just hiring a dev.
We’re onboarding the architect of the next era in care.
If you're ready to build AI with ethics, elegance, and emotional intelligence, apply now.

Salary

$60,000 - $90,000 per year

data.title: AI/ML Engineer
data.descriptionHtml:
Job Summary
We are seeking a skilled AI/ML Engineer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate has a strong foundation in machine learning, data processing, and model deployment, with hands-on experience across multiple ML frameworks. You will be responsible for designing, training, and deploying AI-driven solutions that support production environments and meet the needs of our clients. This role requires analytical thinking, attention to detail, and the ability to work independently in an Agile environment.

Duties

  • Design, implement, and evaluate machine learning models for classification, regression, and recommendation tasks.
  • Preprocess and analyze structured and unstructured datasets to extract meaningful features.
  • Develop and maintain ML pipelines using Python and frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, or Scikit-learn.
  • Deploy lightweight and scalable models for real-time inference in cloud or edge environments.
  • Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate AI/ML solutions into applications.
  • Conduct experiments, document results, and iterate based on performance metrics.
  • Stay updated on recent AI/ML research, frameworks, and best practices.
  • Participate in Agile workflows, including sprint planning and stand-up meetings.

Skills

  • Strong proficiency in Python and ML libraries (PyTorch, TensorFlow, Scikit-learn).
  • Experience with data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model evaluation.
  • Knowledge of deep learning architectures (CNNs, RNNs, Transformers).
  • Familiarity with cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, or GCP for ML deployment.
  • Familiarity with AI and chatbot development.
  • Experience with applications that utilize Large Language Models (LLMs).
  • Experience with database systems (SQL, NoSQL) for data handling and storage.
  • Understanding of software development best practices, including version control (Git).
  • Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to work both independently and collaboratively.
  • Passion for AI/ML technologies and eagerness to deliver innovative solutions.

Job Types: Full-time, Part-time, Contract, Temporary, Internship

Pay: $7.25 - $30.00 per hour

Work Location: Remote

data.title: Azure AI Engineer / Azure AI Specialist
data.descriptionHtml:
Everything To Gain is on the hunt for an Azure AI Engineer / Azure AI Specialist who is passionate about leveraging the power of artificial intelligence to transform business processes and drive innovation. In this pivotal role, you will design, implement, and manage AI solutions using Azure AI services, including Azure Machine Learning and Cognitive Services. You will work closely with cross-functional teams to understand requirements and deliver intelligent solutions that meet client needs. If you are enthusiastic about AI, cloud technologies, and have a strong foundation in data science, we would love to have you on our team!


Responsibilities

  • Develop and deploy AI models using Azure Machine Learning and other AI tools/services within the Azure ecosystem.
  • Work with data scientists and developers to integrate AI solutions into existing applications.
  • Conduct model evaluation and optimization to ensure performance and reliability.
  • Collaborate with stakeholders to define requirements and deliver tailored AI solutions.
  • Stay current with AI trends and advancements within the Azure platform.

Requirements

  • Strong experience with Azure AI services, including Azure Machine Learning and Cognitive Services.
  • Proficient in programming languages such as Python or R for data analysis and model building.
  • Understanding of machine learning concepts, data preprocessing, and model evaluation.
  • Familiarity with cloud services and deployment practices.
  • Experience with data visualization tools and techniques.
  • Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.
  • Strong communication skills to articulate technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Benefits

  • Unlimited paid time off – we trust you to balance your work and life
  • Remote-first – work from anywhere in the world
  • Tech setup – we’ll provide equipment if needed, based on role requirements
  • Work closely with founders and take a lead role in shaping a fast-growing company’s visual identity
  • Join a high-performance, design-forward culture that values creativity, autonomy, and impact

data.title: AI Engineer
data.descriptionHtml:
Please Note: This role is in-office in San Francisco at our headquarters, working with the entire company five days per week. We are not open to remote candidates.

About Us

Campfire is on a mission to redefine the accounting software landscape by taking on giants like Netsuite to build modern accounting software for startups and mid-size tech companies. We graduated from Y Combinator's Summer 2023 cohort, and we are backed by prominent investors like Foundation Capital and a rapidly growing customer base.

The Role

Join our team as an AI Engineer at Campfire, where you'll design and implement AI-driven solutions that supercharge our accounting platform. From automating financial workflows to building intelligent features that provide real-time insights, you’ll be at the forefront of making accounting smarter, faster, and more intuitive for our customers.

We Need Someone Who

Has Expertise:

  • Strong background in machine learning, deep learning, and natural language processing (NLP).

  • Proven experience with frameworks like PyTorch or TensorFlow, and proficiency in Python.

  • Hands-on experience deploying ML models into production environments.

  • Familiarity with LLMs (e.g., OpenAI, Hugging Face) and fine-tuning for real-world use cases.

Thrives in Agility:

  • Our team is lean and moves quickly. You’re comfortable experimenting, iterating, and shipping fast.

Values Autonomy:

  • You take ownership end-to-end — from prototyping models to deploying and monitoring them in production.

Ideal Candidate

  • You’re not just looking for a job; you’re seeking a challenge.

  • You’re passionate about applying AI to solve real business problems.

  • You want to build practical, customer-facing applications of AI rather than just research.

  • You’re eager to collaborate cross-functionally with engineering, product, and design in a fast-paced startup environment.

Let’s Connect

Think you’re the perfect fit? We’re excited to meet you! Reach out, share your story, and let’s explore how you can bring intelligence to Campfire’s mission.

Benefits

We provide top decile benefits, including:

  • 100% premium coverage for employees and 80% coverage for dependents

  • Comprehensive healthcare and dental care options

Careers at Disruptive Tech Solutions

Join a team that is driving innovation in the software design and architecture industry. At Disruptive Tech Solutions, we pride ourselves on a culture that blends technical excellence with creativity and collaboration. Our workplace is fast-paced and tech-savvy, yet supportive and nurturing – a place where your ideas truly can become the next big product. We value continuous learning, so you’ll find opportunities to upskill in the latest technologies, be it cloud, data science, or new development frameworks. As a company that turns ideas into reality, we encourage our team members to think outside the box, challenge the status quo, and grow their careers in the process.

Innovation:
We embrace new ideas and technologies, encouraging our team to experiment and stay ahead of the curve.

Quality & Integrity:
Delivering top-notch solutions with honest work ethics is non-negotiable. We do what’s right for our clients, every time.

Collaboration:
Open communication and teamwork define our daily work. From management to junior developers, everyone’s voice is heard and respected.

Growth & Learning:
Whether through hackathons, training programs, or attending industry conferences, we invest in our employees’ professional development.

We believe productivity comes with balance. Flexible schedules, remote work options, and a supportive environment help our team excel without burnout.


AI/ML Engineer


Jacksonville, FL | Full-Time, On-Site

  • Build predictive models and expose them via REST APIs for tenant churn, rent optimization, etc.
  • Design ETL pipelines for structured and IoT data using Databricks and Azure Synapse.
  • Automate model validation, retraining, and A/B testing using MLOps best practices.
  • Create visual analytics dashboards using Angular, Highcharts, and Power BI.
  • Collaborate with .NET teams to integrate ML services into production APIs.
  • Lead R&D on LLMs and computer vision solutions for property management applications.

data.title: AI Agent Engineer
data.descriptionHtml:
Location: Irvine, CA (onsite; relocation assistance available)
Type: Full-time, early engineering hire
Compensation: Competitive salary + meaningful equity


About Us

Partner directly with our founding team at a fast-growing well-capitalized startup operating at the intersection of consumer hardware and AI. Starting with developing ai agents for our golf coaching service copilot. We're seeking extremely talented devs to our fast growing company. Must have experience developing single and multi-agent applications, full stack applications, traditional ML, and computer vision. And you should be able to do so in about one-third the time that most average people think possible. Good communication skills are essential. Expect talented, motivated, intense and interesting co-workers. Must be willing to relocate to the Orange County, California area (we will help cover moving costs).

We already have significant traction, we're the #1 most used golf simulator in the world, we grow at 1000% YoY, are the #1 best selling golf training product globally, consist of a team of 20, and turn a significant profit.

What You’ll Do

  • Build and deploy LLM-powered coaching assistants that scale personalized golf instruction for thousands of lessons.
  • Retrain and optimize computer vision models for real-time on-device pose estimation, swing analysis, and object detection.
  • Integrate synthetic video generation into the coaching workflow to deliver automated, high-quality instructional content.
  • Own projects end-to-end across backend, mobile, and frontend to turn R&D into production-ready features.
  • Lead high-leverage, high-impact initiatives that drive 10x–100x growth in AI coaching capabilities.

What You’ll Need

  • Proven experience with LLM agents or similar orchestration tools (LangGraph, LangChain, etc.)
  • Hands-on expertise in computer vision (pose estimation, regression, object detection) and model deployment
  • Strong full-stack development skills in production environments
  • Exceptional problem-solving skills, rapid execution, and ability to thrive in a fast-moving startup
  • Excellent communication and collaboration skills—you’ll be working across multiple domains
  • Comfortable working onsite in Irvine, CA

Roadmap

Initial 1 Month

  • Build foundational LLM agent workflows for coaching assistants.
  • Retrain and deploy on-device computer vision models for pose estimation.
  • Collaborate with the biomechanics lab to understand current model limitations.
  • Begin contributing to backend, frontend, and mobile infrastructure.

3–6 Months

  • Own AI agent pipelines end-to-end, including automated video generation.
  • Develop new synthetic media workflows to scale coaching content.
  • Tackle high-leverage projects driving 10x–100x growth in AI coaching capabilities.
  • Optimize model performance for real-time deployment across mobile apps.

6+ Months

  • Lead AI technical initiatives and mentor newer engineers.
  • Define long-term AI roadmap and production standards.
  • Influence company-wide technical strategy for AI-driven coaching.
  • Explore new AI applications in sports simulation and synthetic media.

Why This Role Is Unique

  • Accelerated Impact: Your contributions will shape the future of AI coaching and the direction of the company from day one.
  • Equity & Ownership: Meaningful equity ensures you share in the company’s success.
  • Cutting-Edge Technology: Work at the intersection of AI, computer vision, synthetic media, and sports tech.
  • Elite Team & Culture: Join a small, high-energy, high-velocity team of ambitious engineers, scientists, and creators.
  • Rapid Growth & Career Trajectory: Expect to move into a technical leadership position within months, not years.
Location: Irvine, CA

data.title: AI Simulation engineer
data.descriptionHtml:
Established in 2017, WeRide (NASDAQ: WRD) is a leading global commercial-stage company that develops autonomous driving technologies from Level 2 to Level 4. WeRide is the only tech company in the world that holds driverless permits in China, the UAE, Singapore and the US, conducting autonomous driving R&D, tests and operations in over 30 cities of 10 countries around the world. WeRide has operated a self-driving fleet for more than 2,200 days.

At WeRide, we are dedicated to developing efficient autonomous driving algorithms and evaluation systems to enhance and optimize our autonomous driving technology. This role will focus on researching AI-based approaches and deploy them on simulation tools to facilitate AV algorithm development and validation.

What you will do:

  • Generate simulation scenario with fidelity
  • Develop reasonably-behaving agents interacting with AV algorithm
  • Develop AI-based methodology to evaluate simulation result

Requirements:

  • Have strong expertise in at least one of these machine learning fields: prediction, computer vision, LLM, reinforcement learning; or have strong skills in both algorithms and C++ coding
  • Good communication skills
  • Self-motivated and believe in the future of simulation for AV industry


Plus:

  • Rich experience in world model development
  • Rich experience in computer vision or lidar detection model
  • Rich experience in obstacle prediction/end-to-end AV model development
  • Rich experience in planning and control
  • Publications on top-tier conferences and journals

data.descriptionHtml:
Our client is an innovative AI company building the future of healthcare with AI doctors and nurses, starting in Latin America. Their mission is to reinvent healthcare delivery in the region with AI-native medical solutions. This is an urgent hiring process for a high-impact role. You will have a unique opportunity to be the first AI Engineer in the San Francisco office, helping to shape both the product and the team from the ground up.

Our client is seeking an experienced AI Engineer with a strong backend focus. This is a role for a hands-on builder who can quickly translate non-technical requirements from a strong medical team into production-ready code. You will own product features end-to-end, from conception to deployment, and will have the potential to lead the AI engineering team in the SF office.

You will be responsible for:

  • Developing and deploying Python microservices using FastAPI.
  • Implementing LLM orchestration with tools like LangChain or CrewAI.
  • Building frontend prototypes using React/Tailwind or Flutter.
  • Applying production experience with RAG, vector databases, and evaluation systems.
  • Designing and implementing data pipeline architectures for AI applications.
  • Working closely with the medical team to translate clinical requirements into AI solutions.

Requirements

We are looking for a fast-moving, hands-on engineer who has a proven ability to ship quickly and reliably.

Must-Haves:

  • 2–5 years of experience in AI application development with a heavy backend focus.
  • Proven ability to ship quickly without sacrificing quality.
  • Familiarity with top AI companies and a sense of "what great looks like."
  • Strong experience with Python microservices (FastAPI) and LLM orchestration (LangChain, CrewAI).
  • Hands-on experience with AI agents, APIs, RAG, and vector databases.
  • Openness to working on-site in one of the listed locations: San Francisco, São Paulo, or Medellín.

Bonus Points:

  • A background in Physics or Math.
  • Experience in healthcare AI.
  • Fluency in Spanish or Portuguese.
  • Experience at a top AI company like OpenAI, Anthropic, or DeepMind.

Benefits

  • Salary: $100,000–$300,000
  • Equity: Generous
  • Visa Sponsorship: Not specified

Due to the high volume of applications we anticipate, we regret that we are unable to provide individual feedback to all candidates. If you do not hear back from us within 4 weeks of your application, please assume that you have not been successful on this occasion. We genuinely appreciate your interest and wish you the best in your job search.

Our goal is to foster a diverse, inclusive workplace with equal opportunities for all. If you need any reasonable adjustments during any part of the hiring process or you would like to see the job-advert in an accessible format please let us know at the earliest opportunity by emailing human-resources@mlabs.city.

This information is managed securely in accordance with MLabs Ltd’s Privacy Policy and Information Security Policy, and in compliance with applicable data protection laws. Your data may be shared only with clients and trusted partners where necessary for recruitment purposes. AI and Machine Learning Engineer I Graduate

This role has been designed as ‘Hybrid’ with an expectation that you will work on average 2 days per week from an HPE office.

Who We Are:

Hewlett Packard Enterprise is the global edge-to-cloud company advancing the way people live and work. We help companies connect, protect, analyze, and act on their data and applications wherever they live, from edge to cloud, so they can turn insights into outcomes at the speed required to thrive in today’s complex world. Our culture thrives on finding new and better ways to accelerate what’s next. We know varied backgrounds are valued and succeed here. We have the flexibility to manage our work and personal needs. We make bold moves, together, and are a force for good. If you are looking to stretch and grow your career our culture will embrace you. Open up opportunities with HPE.

Job Description:


Responsibilities:

  • Designs, develops and implements AI and machine learning models. This includes data pre-processing, feature engineering, algorithm selection, model training, and evaluation.
  • Gathers and analyzes relevant data sets to train and test machine learning (ML) models. Understands data analysis techniques, statistical methods, and data visualization to gain insights from the data and make informed decisions.
  • Optimizing algorithms and models to improve their performance is an essential responsibility for AI and Machine Learning Engineers. This involves fine-tuning hyperparameters, conducting experiments, implementing optimization techniques, and employing feature selection or dimensionality reduction methods.
  • Works closely with cross-functional teams, including data scientists, software engineers, product managers, and domain experts. Collaboration is crucial for understanding project requirements, aligning objectives, and integrating AI/ML solutions into existing systems or products.
  • Keeping accurate and up-to-date AI and machine learning project documentation. Document work, including methodologies, code, and experimental results. Responsible for preparing reports and presenting findings or recommendations to stakeholders.
  • Participates in regular design review sessions with the engineering manager, team leader, and other stakeholders to ensure that design choices align with project requirements and best practices.
  • Actively seeks and incorporates feedback from the engineering manager or team leader during the design and implementation phases to ensure continuous improvement and adherence to project goals.
  • Attends daily or weekly stand-up meetings led by the engineering manager or team lead providing updates on progress, discuss challenges, and coordinate efforts with other team members.
  • Prepares and delivers detailed presentations and reports to stakeholders as directed by the engineering manager and team lead, ensuring that complex technical information is communicated clearly and effectively.
  • May be required to interpret and report data findings and maintain or update specific business intelligence tools, databases, dashboards, systems, or methods.

Education and Experience Required:

  • Bachelor's degree in computer science, engineering, data science, machine learning, artificial intelligence, or closely related quantitative discipline. Master’s degree is desirable.
  • Typically, 0-2 years’ experience.

Knowledge and Skills:

  • Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, or Java is required. Knowledge of libraries and frameworks commonly used in AI and machine learning, such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, or scikit-learn, is highly beneficial.
  • A solid understanding of statistics, probability, linear algebra, calculus, and optimization methods is crucial for building and evaluating machine learning models.
  • In-depth knowledge of machine learning algorithms, techniques, and concepts is essential. This includes supervised and unsupervised learning, deep learning, neural networks, reinforcement learning, and natural language processing.
  • Proficiency in working with large datasets, data pre-processing, data cleaning, and exploratory data analysis is necessary. Experience with SQL and databases and data visualization tools like Matplotlib or Tableau is required.

Additional Skills:

What We Can Offer You:

Health & Wellbeing

We strive to provide our team members and their loved ones with a comprehensive suite of benefits that supports their physical, financial and emotional wellbeing.

Personal & Professional Development

We also invest in your career because the better you are, the better we all are. We have specific programs catered to helping you reach any career goals you have — whether you want to become a knowledge expert in your field or apply your skills to another division.

Unconditional Inclusion

We are unconditionally inclusive in the way we work and celebrate individual uniqueness. We know varied backgrounds are valued and succeed here. We have the flexibility to manage our work and personal needs. We make bold moves, together, and are a force for good.

data.title: Lead AI Engineer
data.descriptionHtml:
Become a part of our caring community and help us put health first

We are seeking Lead AI Engineers who has extensive hands-on experience developing Python-based applications intended for use by others, beyond just building models or conducting data analysis. The traditional candidate will have a strong background in both traditional machine learning and emerging generative AI technologies.

As a Lead AI Engineer, you will play a key role in developing and deploying innovative AI-powered solutions, working with large-scale datasets and cutting-edge tools to solve complex business challenges. You will collaborate closely with data scientists and fellow engineers, contributing to the entire AI development lifecycle from data ingestion to software deployment and monitoring.


Key Responsibilities:

  • Explore and implement generative AI technologies using Large Language Models and other generative models to create innovative solutions.
  • Build and maintain robust APIs for enabling Retrieval-Augmented Generation and generative AI agents within business use cases.
  • Design, develop, and maintain robust data pipelines for ingestion, processing, and transformation of large datasets.
  • Assist our data science team in the development and deployment of traditional machine learning models.
  • Collaborate with data scientists to understand model requirements and translate them into scalable engineering solutions.
  • Monitor and maintain performance and reliability of deployed APIs, models, and data pipelines.
  • Stay up to date with the latest advancements in machine learning, generative AI, and related technologies.


Use your skills to make an impact

Required Qualifications

  • Bachelor's Degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g., Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, or a related field) with a minimum of 5 years of professional experience; OR
  • Master's Degree in a similar field with at least 5 years of relevant experience.
  • 7+ years of Python application development and data manipulation libraries (e.g., Pandas, NumPy).
  • Familiarity with API frameworks (e.g., FastAPI, Flask) and RESTful API concepts.
  • Strong understanding of machine learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn).
  • Familiarity with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Google Cloud, Azure)
  • 3+ years of experience with containerization (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes).
  • 3+ years of experience with CI/CD tools, pipelines
  • Experience working with Large Language Model (LLM) in application development
  • Experience with version control systems (e.g., Git) and software development best practices.

Preferred Qualifications

  • Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to work in a collaborative environment.
  • Knowledge of generative AI frameworks such as Langchain or Pydantic AI.
  • Experience deploying software using tools like Docker and Kubernetes.
  • Experience with deep learning techniques and frameworks.

Description:
Are you ready to join a team of innovators and play a critical role in shaping the future of Artificial Intelligence? We're seeking a highly motivated and experienced Artificial Intelligence Engineer to join our Lockheed Martin Artificial Intelligence Center (LAIC) team. As a key member of our Applied AI team, you'll have the opportunity to work on high-impact projects, develop and apply cutting-edge AI technologies, and collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive innovation and experimentation.

What you'll be doing:

  • Develop and apply current AI paradigms, including computer vision, deep learning, and reinforcement learning, to solve complex signal processing problems and field innovative solutions.
  • Engage in every phase of the system development lifecycle, including requirements generation, system and software design, implementation, integration, and flight test.
  • Take ownership of critical tasks and lead technical teams to deliver high-quality solutions.
  • Participate in the development of proposals and whitepapers to secure funding for AI research and development projects.
  • Assume technical lead responsibilities and mentor junior engineers to help them develop their skills and expertise.
  • Work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to develop and deploy AI solutions.
  • Communicate complex technical concepts and solutions to non-technical stakeholders.

What's In It For You:

We offer flexible work schedules and comprehensive benefits, investing in your future and security. Learn more about Lockheed Martin's comprehensive benefits package here.

  • A strong background in software engineering, artificial intelligence, and machine learning.

  • Experience with current AI paradigms, including computer vision, deep learning, and reinforcement learning.
  • Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, Java, or C++.
  • Self-motivation, strong work ethic, and time management skills.
  • Excellent interpersonal and communication skills.
  • A Bachelor's degree in a relevant field, such as computer science, electrical engineering, or mathematics, and 5+ years of experience in AI or a related field.

Work Location:

data.title: Software Engineer, AI, Customer Claims & Support
data.descriptionHtml:
What to Expect

Tesla's service software team powers intelligent systems across insurance claims systems, internal service tool, customer service, global operations, and innovative features like autonomous agents for sustainable energy solutions. At Tesla, you'll collaborate with some of the most brilliant engineers globally, engaging in cutting-edge AI development to create responsive agents that enhance user experiences across various modalities, including voice, text, and more.

The team is seeking a Software Engineer proficient in Python and AI technologies to join and work on building advanced AI agents for applications such as automated customer support, knowledge-driven decision-making, and intelligent workflows. The engineer will collaborate with skilled software engineers, data scientists, product managers, and end-users to turn visionary AI concepts into reality.


What You'll Do

  • Design and build secure, intuitive, and efficient AI agents across multiple modalities (e.g., voice, text, or multi-modal interfaces), integrating them seamlessly into Tesla's ecosystem for tasks like real-time query handling and automated workflows
  • Quickly grasp new concepts in AI, such as developing diverse agent interfaces, and apply your knowledge to integrate with knowledge bases and transactional systems using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) techniques
  • Push your first pull request (PR) with your own code to Tesla's AI platform in your first week
  • Form data contracts (e.g., using protobuf or APIs) with partner teams for the pragmatic implementation of scalable AI features, designed in concert with engineering, product, and design teams
  • Own a portion of the AI agent codebase, focusing on quality, performance, and cross-modality integration; write documentation, review code from team members, and ensure robust handling of edge cases like variable input types or high-latency RAG queries
  • Focus on keeping processes, code, and tooling as safe, fast, and reliable as our AI systems; elevate standards across teams to enhance work experiences while delivering value to users
  • Use first principles thinking to continually optimize AI processes and practices, such as refining RAG pipelines for faster retrieval and better accuracy, ultimately providing superior experiences for customers and accelerating sustainable energy transitions


What You'll Bring

  • Having experience in shipping secure, scalable AI applications, with a focus on agent-based systems across modalities (e.g., voice integration using libraries like liveKit, various STT & TTS providers, text-based agents, or multi-modal setups)
  • Sound knowledge and hands-on experience with Python for AI development, including building and integrating RAG systems (e.g., using LangChain, FAISS, or Pinecone for knowledge base retrieval)
  • Excellent knowledge of modern programming languages and AI tools (Python, TypeScript, etc.), with experience in creating RAG pipelines, integrating with transactional systems (e.g., databases like PostgreSQL or APIs for real-time data), and handling diverse data processing needs
  • Professional or personal experience building products in domains like AI agents, natural language processing (NLP), voice assistants, knowledge management systems, or multi-modal AI is a plus
  • Passion for Tesla’s mission of accelerating the world’s transition to sustainable energy, with a drive to innovate in AI for real-world impact


Compensation and Benefits
Benefits

Along with competitive pay, as a full-time Tesla employee, you are eligible for the following benefits at day 1 of hire:

  • Aetna PPO and HSA plans > 2 medical plan options with $0 payroll deduction
  • Family-building, fertility, adoption and surrogacy benefits
  • Dental (including orthodontic coverage) and vision plans, both have options with a $0 paycheck contribution
  • Company Paid (Health Savings Account) HSA Contribution when enrolled in the High Deductible Aetna medical plan with HSA
  • Healthcare and Dependent Care Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA)
  • 401(k) with employer match, Employee Stock Purchase Plans, and other financial benefits
  • Company paid Basic Life, AD&D, short-term and long-term disability insurance
  • Employee Assistance Program
  • Sick and Vacation time (Flex time for salary positions), and Paid Holidays
  • Back-up childcare and parenting support resources
  • Voluntary benefits to include: critical illness, hospital indemnity, accident insurance, theft & legal services, and pet insurance
  • Weight Loss and Tobacco Cessation Programs
  • Tesla Babies program
  • Commuter benefits
  • Employee discounts and perks program
Expected Compensation
$133,440 - $200,160/annual salary + cash and stock awards + benefits

Pay offered may vary depending on multiple individualized factors, including market location, job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. The total compensation package for this position may also include other elements dependent on the position offered. Details of participation in these benefit plans will be provided if an employee receives an offer of employment.


Tesla is an Equal Opportunity / Affirmative Action employer committed to diversity in the workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, age, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, gender identity or any other factor protected by applicable federal, state or local laws.

Tesla is also committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodations to individuals with disabilities. Please let your recruiter know if you need an accommodation at any point during the interview process.
